wesm commented on a change in pull request #2672: ARROW-3377: [Gandiva][C++] Replace If statement with bit operations for bitmap
URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/2672#discussion_r221567319



 ##########
 File path: cpp/src/gandiva/precompiled/bitmap.cc
 ##########
 @@ -38,11 +38,7 @@ FORCE_INLINE
 void bitMapSetBit(unsigned char* bmap, int position, bool value) {
   int byteIdx = POS_TO_BYTE_INDEX(position);
   int bitIdx = POS_TO_BIT_INDEX(position);
-  if (value) {
-    bmap[byteIdx] |= (1 << bitIdx);
-  } else {
-    bmap[byteIdx] &= ~(1 << bitIdx);
-  }
+  bmap[byteIdx] ^= (-value ^ bmap[byteIdx]) & (1UL << bitIdx);

 Review comment:
   There is some redundancy here with arrow/util/bit-util.h. We should explore merging these together

